Android Studio:
    When you start one emulator (virtual device):
    What happens internally:
    1️⃣ Emulator process starts on your PC
    2️⃣ It opens two ports automatically
    Example:
    5554 → Console port
    5555 → ADB communication port
    3️⃣ Inside emulator → adbd (ADB daemon) starts
    4️⃣ On your PC → adb server (port 5037) is already running
    5️⃣ adb server connects to emulator’s ADB port (5555)
    6️⃣ Device gets registered in adb device list ✅


ADB: ( Android Debugging Bridge )
🔹 1️⃣ ADB Architecture (Complete Flow)
ADB = 3 components:
1️⃣ ADB Client
→ Command you type (adb devices, adb install)
2️⃣ ADB Server
→ Background process on PC (port 5037)
3️⃣ adbd (Daemon)
→ Runs inside Android device/emulator

ADB Commands:

adb devices          → Check connected devices/emulators
adb install app.apk  → Install APK manually
adb uninstall packagename    → Remove installed app
adb shell            → Enter device command line
adb logcat           → View real-time device logs
adb kill-server      → Stop adb server (reset connection)
adb start-server     → Start adb server again
adb forward          → Forward PC port → device port (used by Appium UiAutomator2)
adb reverse          → Reverse device port → PC port
adb shell pm list packages → List installed packages
adb shell dumpsys activity → Get current running activity
adb shell am start   → Launch specific activity manually
adb shell getprop    → Get device system properties


