Pytest Hooks:
------------
1. Special functions that run automatically before/after tests without calling manually.
2.Yes bro ✅ — hooks go inside conftest.py.
👉 Because:
• Pytest auto-detects hooks there
• Applies to all tests
• No import needed
3.Core lifecycle = basic hooks needed 👍
        ✅ Background → foreground recovery (very important)
    Appium defines 5 possible states
    driver.query_app_state(package) returns number showing app state
    States:

    • 0 → Not installed
    • 1 → Not running
    • 2 → Running in background (suspended)
    • 3 → Running in background
    • 4 → Running in foreground ✅
